{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870552852,"sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a22287f001vXd37gEFoIuBlS","messageID":"msg_d7a221eda001hLb0GLYQY6qlVI","sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d00a02ee93b448ac98b675b3147d3133","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status Commands Design Document\n2: \n3: **AR**: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令  \n4: **Module**: cmd/cli  \n5: **Language**: Python  \n6: **Size**: M\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: The `invoke` and `status` commands are essential components of the AgentCube CLI that enable users to interact with deployed AI agents. The `invoke` command sends requests to published agent endpoints with optional payloads and custom headers, while the `status` command provides visibility into agent deployment state and health. Both commands support multiple providers: the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service).\n11: \n12: ## Background\n13: \n14: AgentCube users need to interact with their deployed AI agents after the publish process completes. This includes:\n15: \n16: 1. **Invocation**: Sending requests to agents with custom payloads, managing session IDs, and receiving responses\n17: 2. **Status Monitoring**: Checking deployment health, endpoint availability, and runtime status\n18: 3. **Multi-provider Support**: Working with both AgentCube CRs and standard Kubernetes deployments\n19: 4. **Flexible Configuration**: Supporting custom headers, different payload formats, and provider-specific options\n20: \n21: The invoke/status commands complete the lifecycle management flow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status), providing users with full control over their AI agents.\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### Component Diagram\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────┐\n29: │   CLI (Typer)   │\n30: │  main.py     │\n31: └──────┬──────┘\n32:        │\n33:        ├──► invoke() ───► InvokeRuntime ───► HTTP Client\n34:        │                  invoke_runtime.py         │\n35:        │                                            ├──► AgentCube Provider (CR)\n36:        │                                            └──► Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n37:        │\n38:        └──► status() ───► StatusRuntime ───► K8s Client\n39:                           status_runtime.py         │\n40:                                                    ├──► AgentRuntime CR Status\n41:                                                    └──► Deployment/Service Status\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Layer Architecture\n45: \n46: ```\n47: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n48: │         CLI Layer (agentcube/cli/main.py)    │\n49: │  • Typer command definitions               │\n50: │  • User input validation                   │\n51: │  • Rich output formatting                  │\n52: │  • Error handling and user feedback        │\n53: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n54:                     │\n55:                     ▼\n56: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n57: │     Runtime Layer (agentcube/runtime/)     │\n58: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n59: │  │  InvokeRuntime  │  │  StatusRuntime  │  │\n60: │  │  invoke_runtime.py││ status_runtime.py│  │\n61: │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n62: │  • Command orchestration                   │\n63: │  • Provider selection                      │\n64: │  • Session management                      │\n65: │  • Endpoint resolution                     │\n66: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n67:                     │\n68:                     ▼\n69: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n70: │      Service Layer (agentcube/services/)   │\n71: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n72: │  │AgentCubeProvider│  │KubernetesProvider│ │\n73: │  │agentcube_       │  │k8s_provider.py  │  │\n74: │  │provider.py      │  │                 │  │\n75: │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n76: │  • AgentRuntime CR operations              │\n77: │  • K8s Deployment/Service operations       │\n78: │  • Metadata management                     │\n79: │  • Status aggregation                      │\n80: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n81:                     │\n82:                     ▼\n83: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n84: │    HTTP / K8s Client Layer                  │\n85: │  • httpx.AsyncClient (async HTTP requests) │\n86: │  • kubernetes.KubernetesClient (K8s API)   │\n87: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Key Components\n91: \n92: 1. **CLI Layer** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n93:    - `invoke()`: Typer command for invoking agents\n94:    - `status()`: Typer command for checking agent status\n95:    - Payload and header parsing\n96:    - Provider selection\n97:    - Rich table formatting for status output\n98: \n99: 2. **Runtime Layer**\n100:    - `InvokeRuntime`: Orchestration of agent invocation\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 1136. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status Commands Design Document\n\n**AR**: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` commands are essential components of the AgentCube CLI that enable users to interact with deployed AI agents. The `invoke` command sends requests to published agent endpoints with optional payloads and custom headers, while the `status` command provides visibility into agent deployment state and health. Both commands support multiple providers: the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service).\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube users need to interact with their deployed AI agents after the publish process completes. This includes:\n\n1. **Invocation**: Sending requests to agents with custom payloads, managing session IDs, and receiving responses\n2. **Status Monitoring**: Checking deployment health, endpoint availability, and runtime status\n3. **Multi-provider Support**: Working with both AgentCube CRs and standard Kubernetes deployments\n4. **Flexible Configuration**: Supporting custom headers, different payload formats, and provider-specific options\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775870552832,"end":1775870552850}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870552856,"sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a222ae40016dZFwH5cyt2P33","messageID":"msg_d7a221eda001hLb0GLYQY6qlVI","sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-25f312c3249d4974a6e0ae25f507a97b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n4: **Language**: Python\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Verify invoke command interface in main.py\n11: - [ ] Verify invoke command exists in agentcube/cli/main.py\n12: - [ ] Verify all required parameters are defined:\n13:   - [ ] workspace (default \".\", short flag \"-f\")\n14:   - [ ] payload (default \"{}\")\n15:   - [ ] header_list (optional, can be specified multiple times)\n16:   - [ ] provider (default \"agentcube\")\n17:   - [ ] verbose (default False)\n18: - [ ] Verify parameter types match design (str, Optional[str], List[str], bool)\n19: - [ ] Verify help text is present for all parameters\n20: - [ ] Verify command docstring describes functionality\n21: - [ ] Verify JSON payload validation is implemented\n22: - [ ] Verify header parsing is implemented correctly\n23: \n24: **Verification**: Run `agentcube invoke --help` and verify all parameters are displayed correctly\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ### Task 2: Verify status command interface in main.py\n29: - [ ] Verify status command exists in agentcube/cli/main.py\n30: - [ ] Verify all required parameters are defined:\n31:   - [ ] workspace (default \".\", short flag \"-f\")\n32:   - [ ] provider (default \"agentcube\")\n33:   - [ ] verbose (default False)\n34: - [ ] Verify parameter types match design (str, bool)\n35: - [ ] Verify help text is present for all parameters\n36: - [ ] Verify command docstring describes functionality\n37: - [ ] Verify status output formatting is implemented\n38: \n39: **Verification**: Run `agentcube status --help` and verify all parameters are displayed correctly\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Task 3: Verify InvokeRuntime class structure\n44: - [ ] Verify InvokeRuntime class exists in agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n45: - [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose and provider parameters\n46: - [ ] Verify logging is configured based on verbose flag\n47: - [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n48: - [ ] Verify imports are correct (asyncio, httpx, logging, etc.)\n49: \n50: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime; r = InvokeRuntime(); print(r)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### Task 4: Verify StatusRuntime class structure\n55: - [ ] Verify StatusRuntime class exists in agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n56: - [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose and provider parameters\n57: - [ ] Verify logging is configured based on verbose flag\n58: - [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n59: - [ ] Verify imports are correct (MetadataService, AgentCubeProvider, KubernetesProvider)\n60: \n61: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime; r = StatusRuntime(); print(r)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Task 5: Verify InvokeRuntime.invoke method signature and structure\n66: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts workspace_path: Path parameter\n67: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts payload: Dict[str, Any] parameter\n68: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] parameter\n69: - [ ] Verify return type is Any\n70: - [ ] Verify method calls _validate_invoke_prerequisites\n71: - [ ] Verify method handles AgentCube provider endpoint formatting\n72: - [ ] Verify method adds session_id header if available\n73: - [ ] Verify method calls _invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n74: - [ ] Verify method falls back to _direct_http_invocation on error\n75: - [ ] Verify comprehensive error handling and logging\n76: \n77: **Verification**: Review invoke_runtime.py and verify method implementation matches design\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Task 6: Verify InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites method\n82: - [ ] Verify method loads metadata using MetadataService\n83: - [ ] Verify method checks agent_id or agent_endpoint exists\n84: - [ ] Verify method raises ValueError if agent not published\n85: - [ ] Verify method extracts endpoint from metadata\n86: - [ ] Verify method raises ValueError if no endpoint found\n87: - [ ] Verify method extracts namespace from metadata\n88: - [ ] Verify method returns metadata, endpoint, namespace tuple\n89: - [ ] Verify error messages are clear and actionable\n90: \n91: **Verification**: Run unit test for _validate_invoke_prerequisites with various metadata states\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Task 7: Verify InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube method\n96: - [ ] Verify method is async\n97: - [ ] Verify method accepts agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path parameters\n98: - [ ] Verify method handles AgentCube provider endpoint formatting\n99: - [ ] Verify method uses httpx.AsyncClient with 60.0 timeout\n100: - [ ] Verify method makes POST request to endpoint\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 1034. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `cmd/cli`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify invoke command interface in main.py\n- [ ] Verify invoke command exists in agentcube/cli/main.py\n- [ ] Verify all required parameters are defined:\n  - [ ] workspace (default \".\", short flag \"-f\")\n  - [ ] payload (default \"{}\")\n  - [ ] header_list (optional, can be specified multiple times)\n  - [ ] provider (default \"agentcube\")\n  - [ ] verbose (default False)\n- [ ] Verify parameter types match design (str, Optional[str], List[str], bool)\n- [ ] Verify help text is present for all parameters\n- [ ] Verify command docstring describes functionality","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775870552836,"end":1775870552853}}}}
