{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870618887,"sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a232cd9001D1kT2GIe12gy2I","messageID":"msg_d7a2324a0001hbih9iL4iXWd1H","sessionID":"ses_285de6bdaffeSCYlWS06GqDtjM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9db294f3a4b541018d286a6ce447bf54","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI\n2: \n3: A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n4: \n5: ## Installation\n6: \n7: ```bash\n8: pip install agentcube\n9: ```\n10: \n11: Or install from source:\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: cd cmd/cli\n15: pip install -e .\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Usage\n19: \n20: The CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.\n21: \n22: ### Pack Command\n23: \n24: Package an agent workspace by validating and preparing it:\n25: \n26: ```bash\n27: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n28: ```\n29: \n30: Options:\n31: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n32: - `--agent-name TEXT`: Override the agent name\n33: - `--language [python|java]`: Programming language\n34: - `--entrypoint TEXT`: Override the entrypoint command\n35: - `--port INTEGER`: Port to expose in the Dockerfile\n36: - `--build-mode [local|cloud]`: Build strategy\n37: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n38: - `--output PATH`: Output path for packaged workspace\n39: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n40: \n41: Example:\n42: \n43: ```bash\n44: kubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python --port 8080\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### Build Command\n48: \n49: Build a container image from the packaged agent workspace:\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: kubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: Options:\n56: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n57: - `-p, --proxy TEXT`: Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n58: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n59: - `--output PATH`: Output path for build artifacts\n60: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n61: \n62: Example:\n63: \n64: ```bash\n65: kubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### Publish Command\n69: \n70: Publish an agent to the specified provider:\n71: \n72: ```bash\n73: kubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n74: ```\n75: \n76: Options:\n77: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n78: - `--version TEXT`: Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n79: - `--image-url TEXT`: Image repository URL\n80: - `--image-username TEXT`: Username for image repository\n81: - `--image-password TEXT`: Password for image repository\n82: - `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n83: - `--region TEXT`: Deployment region\n84: - `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n85: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n86: - `--node-port INTEGER`: Specific NodePort for K8s deployment\n87: - `--replicas INTEGER`: Number of replicas for K8s deployment\n88: - `--namespace TEXT`: The namespace for the deployment\n89: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n90: \n91: Example:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080 --replicas 3\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### Invoke Command\n98: \n99: Invoke a published agent with the given payload:\n100: \n101: ```bash\n102: kubectl-agentcube invoke [OPTIONS]\n103: ```\n104: \n105: Options:\n106: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n107: - `--payload TEXT`: JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n108: - `--header TEXT`: Custom HTTP headers (can be specified multiple times)\n109: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n110: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n111: \n112: Example:\n113: \n114: ```bash\n115: kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello\"}' --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ### Status Command\n119: \n120: Get the status of a published agent:\n121: \n122: ```bash\n123: kubectl-agentcube status [OPTIONS]\n124: ```\n125: \n126: Options:\n127: - `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n128: - `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n129: - `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n130: \n131: Example:\n132: \n133: ```bash\n134: kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ## Metadata File\n138: \n139: The CLI uses an `agent_metadata.yaml` file to store agent configuration:\n140: \n141: ```yaml\n142: agent_name: my-agent\n143: description: My AI agent\n144: language: python\n145: entrypoint: python main.py\n146: port: 8080\n147: build_mode: local\n148: region: us-west-1\n149: version: 0.1.0\n150: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ## Development\n154: \n155: ### Running Tests\n156: \n157: ```bash\n158: pytest tests/\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### Code Quality\n162: \n163: ```bash\n164: ruff check agentcube/\n165: mypy agentcube/\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ## License\n169: \n170: Apache-2.0\n\n(End of file - total 170 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI\n\nA developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube\n```\n\nOr install from source:\n\n```bash\ncd cmd/cli\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md","time":{"start":1775870618871,"end":1775870618885}}}}
